      "content": "but \"rebuilding\" is just another way of saying \"prolonging the misery.\" how do you rebuild when the foundation is completely gone? every time I think about trying again, I just see more debt and more people looking at me with pity. it feels like the only way to actually make the shame stop—to actually give my family peace instead of making them deal with my failure—is to just not be here anymore. does that even make sense? like, isn't it better to just end the cycle now before I cause more damage?",
